{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"798048b0-a77a-4869-8634-9617ee9ca452","content":"Here are common options by framework:\n\n**ASP.NET Core**\n- Template: `dotnet new webapi`\n- Auth options: JWT Bearer, Cookie, Identity, Azure AD/Entra ID, OAuth2/OpenID Connect\n\n**Node.js**\n- Frameworks: Express, Fastify, NestJS\n- Auth options: Passport.js (JWT, OAuth2, Local), express-jwt, Auth0 SDK\n\n**Python**\n- Frameworks: FastAPI, Django REST, Flask\n- Auth options: OAuth2 with JWT (FastAPI built-in), Django auth, Flask-Login\n\n**Java**\n- Template: Spring Boot (`spring-boot-starter-web`)\n- Auth options: Spring Security (JWT, OAuth2, LDAP, SAML)\n\nFor most new projects, **JWT Bearer tokens** with OAuth2/OpenID Connect is the modern standard. Which language/framework are you targeting? I can help scaffold it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"db9e1d95-11b2-4bf1-8995-4665a67ec3f3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most popular frameworks.","outputTokens":278,"requestId":"403B:28F32E:E358C55:FC75501:69EC0E5C"},"id":"6fb5e62c-e353-4877-b641-00466369f170","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:44:21.176Z","parentId":"2b925dfc-eb9e-42ea-b28c-f2e6d08c601d"}
